    {
      "question": "How long will my cabinetry project take from start to finish?",
      "answer": "The timeline for a cabinetry project varies significantly based on the type of cabinets selected and the project''s complexity. \n\n*   **Design Phase:** Typically 1-3 weeks, depending on the number of revisions. \n*   **Ordering/Manufacturing:** \n    *   **Stock Cabinets:** Lead times can be as short as 1-3 weeks if in stock. \n    *   **Semi-Custom Cabinets:** Generally 4-8 weeks for manufacturing and delivery. \n    *   **Custom Cabinets:** Can range from 8-16 weeks or more, depending on complexity and materials. \n*   **Installation:** For an average kitchen, installation usually takes 3-7 days, but larger or more intricate projects can take longer. \n\nWe provide a detailed timeline estimate during the planning phase once your selections are made, keeping you informed every step of the way."
