UPDATE page_sections SET content = '{"content": {
  "title": "Unlock Your Dream Home with Custom Cabinet Building",
  "text": "Tired of generic, ill-fitting cabinets that don''t quite meet your needs? Custom cabinet building offers the ultimate solution, transforming your kitchen, bathroom, home office, or any space into a beautifully organized and highly functional area tailored precisely to your lifestyle. At ProBuddy, we connect you with skilled artisans who craft cabinets designed to perfection.\n\n**Why Choose Custom Cabinets?**\nUnlike off-the-shelf or semi-custom options, custom cabinets are built from scratch to your exact specifications. This means you get to choose every detail: the wood species, finish, hardware, internal organizational features, and dimensions. The result is a perfect fit for unusual layouts, maximized storage in tight spaces, and a truly unique aesthetic that reflects your personal style and enhances your home''s value.\n\n**What to Expect When Hiring a Professional:**\n1.  **Initial Consultation & Design:** A professional cabinet maker will visit your home to take precise measurements, discuss your vision, functional requirements, material preferences, and budget. They''ll often provide 3D renderings or detailed drawings to help you visualize the final product.\n2.  **Material & Finish Selection:** You''ll explore a wide range of options, from durable hardwoods like maple, cherry, and oak to eco-friendly alternatives, laminates, and various paint or stain finishes. Your expert will guide you through the pros and cons of each.\n3.  **Quotation & Agreement:** Based on the design and material choices, you''ll receive a detailed quote. Once approved, a contract outlining the scope of work, timeline, and payment schedule will be signed.\n4.  **Fabrication:** This is where the magic happens! Your cabinets are meticulously built in the workshop by skilled craftsmen, ensuring precision, durability, and a flawless finish.\n5.  **Installation:** The final step involves careful delivery and professional installation in your home. This ensures that your custom cabinets are perfectly level, securely mounted, and fully functional, often including adjustments to doors and drawers.\n\n**Practical Advice for Homeowners:**\n*   **Define Your Needs:** Before the consultation, make a list of what you need your cabinets to do. Do you need spice racks, pull-out pantries, charging stations, or specific drawer organizers?\n*   **Set a Realistic Budget:** Custom work is an investment. Be upfront about your budget, and your professional can guide you on material choices and features that align with it.\n*   **Review Portfolios & References:** Look at examples of past work and read client testimonials to ensure the professional''s style and quality match your expectations.\n*   **Communicate Clearly:** Don''t hesitate to ask questions or express concerns at any stage. Clear communication ensures a smooth process and a satisfying outcome.\n*   **Understand the Timeline:** Custom cabinet building is a detailed process that takes time, from design to fabrication and installation. Be prepared for a realistic timeframe, typically several weeks to a few months.\n\nInvesting in custom cabinets is investing in your home''s beauty, functionality, and longevity. ProBuddy is here to connect you with trusted, experienced professionals who can bring your custom cabinet dreams to life."
}}', updated_at = '2026-02-17T19:48:52.010Z' WHERE id = 'kiu2a50MAEl-B88_68HDM';
UPDATE page_sections SET content = '{
  "faq": {
    "title": "Frequently Asked Questions About Custom Cabinet Building",
    "items": [
      {
        "question": "How much do custom cabinets cost, and what factors influence the price?",
        "answer": "The cost of custom cabinets can vary significantly based on several factors, typically ranging from $500 to $1,500+ per linear foot, with total project costs often between $10,000 and $50,000 or more for a full kitchen. Key factors influencing the price include the type of wood or material chosen (e.g., maple, cherry, oak, walnut, or high-grade plywood with veneers), the complexity of the design (e.g., intricate carvings, specialized storage solutions, custom sizes), the type of finish (e.g., multi-step paint, stain, glaze), hardware selections (e.g., soft-close hinges, drawer slides, decorative pulls), and the labor involved in both fabrication and installation. Higher-end materials, unique designs, and specialized features will naturally increase the overall investment."
      },
      {
        "question": "What is the typical timeline for designing, building, and installing custom cabinets?",
        "answer": "The complete process for custom cabinets, from initial consultation to final installation, typically takes between 6 to 16 weeks, depending on the project''s complexity and the builder''s schedule. The design phase, including consultations, measurements, and revisions, can take 2-4 weeks. Once designs are approved, material sourcing and fabrication usually require 4-10 weeks, as each piece is meticulously crafted. Finally, installation can take 1-2 weeks, depending on the size of the project and any existing demolition work required. We always provide a detailed timeline specific to your project during the initial planning stages."
      },
      {
        "question": "What materials are commonly used for custom cabinets, and how do they impact durability and aesthetics?",
        "answer": "Common materials for custom cabinets include solid hardwoods (such as maple, cherry, oak, and walnut), high-grade plywood (typically Baltic Birch or cabinet-grade plywood), and MDF (Medium-Density Fiberboard) for specific applications like painted doors. Solid hardwoods offer exceptional durability, a natural aesthetic, and can be refinished multiple times. Plywood provides excellent stability, resistance to warping, and is often used for cabinet boxes. MDF is a cost-effective option for painted doors and panels due to its smooth surface and stability, though it''s less durable than solid wood or plywood for structural components. The choice of material impacts not only the look and feel but also the longevity and resilience of your cabinets against daily wear and tear."
      },
      {
        "question": "What is the design process like, and how involved can I be in customizing my cabinets?",
        "answer": "Our design process is highly collaborative and client-centric. It begins with an initial consultation where we discuss your needs, preferences, style, and budget. We then take precise measurements of your space. Our designers will create detailed 3D renderings and floor plans, allowing you to visualize the proposed cabinets in your home. You''ll have multiple opportunities to provide feedback and request revisions until the design perfectly matches your vision. Customization is the core of our service – you can choose everything from the exact dimensions, door styles, wood species, finishes, hardware, and an array of interior storage solutions like pull-out shelves, spice racks, and drawer organizers. We guide you through every decision to ensure the final product is uniquely yours."
      },
      {
        "question": "Why should I choose custom cabinets over stock or semi-custom options?",
        "answer": "Choosing custom cabinets offers unparalleled advantages over stock or semi-custom options, primarily in terms of fit, quality, and personalization. Custom cabinets are built specifically for your space, maximizing every inch and accommodating unique architectural features, resulting in a seamless, built-in look. They are crafted with higher-quality materials and superior construction methods (e.g., dovetail joinery, full-extension soft-close slides) for enhanced durability and longevity. Most importantly, custom cabinets allow for complete design freedom, enabling you to achieve a truly unique aesthetic and highly functional storage solutions tailored precisely to your lifestyle and needs, which can significantly increase your home''s value and enjoyment."
      },
      {
        "question": "What kind of warranty or after-care support do you offer for your custom cabinets?",
        "answer": "We stand behind the quality and craftsmanship of our custom cabinets. We typically offer a comprehensive warranty, often ranging from 5 years to a lifetime, covering materials and workmanship against defects. Details of our specific warranty will be provided in your contract. Beyond the warranty, we are committed to client satisfaction and offer after-care support for any questions or minor adjustments you might need post-installation. We''ll also provide guidance on proper cleaning and maintenance to ensure your custom cabinets remain beautiful and functional for decades to come."
      }
    ]
  }
}', updated_at = '2026-02-17T19:48:54.873Z' WHERE id = 'vVMPpvTFeQp6EIEOB2pF1';
