UPDATE page_sections SET content = '{"tips": {"title": "Deck Staining and Sealing: Tips for Homeowners", "tips": ["**Understand Stain Types:** Before getting quotes, research the difference between clear sealers, semi-transparent stains, and solid stains. Each offers different levels of protection, color, and longevity, impacting the cost and look of your deck.", "**Assess Deck Condition First:** Walk your deck thoroughly. Note any loose boards, protruding nails, or signs of rot. Professionals will address these, but knowing beforehand helps you understand the scope of work and ensures your deck is structurally sound for staining.", "**Get Detailed Quotes:** Don''t just ask for a price. Request a breakdown of their process: what type of cleaner they use, if sanding is included, how many coats of stain, and the specific product brand. This allows for fair comparison between professionals.", "**Verify Credentials & Insurance:** Always ask for proof of liability insurance and relevant licenses. Check references or online reviews to ensure you''re hiring a reputable and reliable professional.", "**Confirm Prep Work:** The longevity of your deck stain heavily relies on proper preparation. Ensure your professional includes thorough cleaning (power washing), and potentially sanding, to remove old stain, dirt, and mildew, creating a perfect surface for new application.", "**Discuss Weather & Curing:** Staining requires specific weather conditions. Confirm the professional''s plan for ideal temperature and humidity, and understand the full curing time. Avoid heavy foot traffic or placing furniture back too soon.", "**Ask About Maintenance:** Once the job is done, inquire about the best practices for maintaining your newly stained deck. Ask about recommended cleaning methods and the expected lifespan of the stain, as well as when reapplication might be needed."]}}', updated_at = '2026-02-17T19:49:03.635Z' WHERE id = 'XpgMOy6lp9VLKt-r_T0ud';
