UPDATE page_sections SET content = '{"content": {
  "title": "Elevate Your Home''s Style: Professional Trim & Molding Installation",
  "text": "Transform the look and feel of your home with expertly installed trim and molding. These architectural details are more than just decorative accents; they provide a polished finish, define spaces, and add significant character and value to any room. From elegant crown molding that draws the eye upward, to sturdy baseboards protecting your walls, and intricate door and window casings, the right trim can dramatically enhance your home''s aesthetic.\n\n**Why Hire a Professional for Trim & Molding?**\nWhile installing trim might seem like a DIY project, achieving a seamless, professional finish requires precision, specialized tools, and extensive experience. Professionals ensure:\n*   **Perfect Mitered Corners:** No unsightly gaps or misalignments.\n*   **Seamless Transitions:** Smooth joints, especially on long runs.\n*   **Proper Fastening:** Secure installation that lasts.\n*   **Efficient Workflow:** Saving you time and hassle.\n*   **Expert Advice:** Guidance on material selection and design.\n\n**What to Expect During Your Installation Project:**\n1.  **Initial Consultation & Measurement:** Your ProBuddy professional will visit your home to discuss your vision, recommend styles, and take precise measurements of the areas where trim will be installed.\n2.  **Material Selection:** Based on your budget and aesthetic goals, you''ll choose from various materials like MDF (cost-effective, paintable), solid wood (durable, stainable, classic look), or PVC (moisture-resistant for bathrooms).\n3.  **Preparation:** Before installation begins, ensure the work area is clear. Your pro may need to remove old trim, repair minor wall imperfections, or protect flooring.\n4.  **Precision Cutting & Installation:** Using specialized saws and tools, the trim will be cut to exact specifications, mitered for perfect corners, and securely fastened to walls, ceilings, or doorframes using nails and adhesive where necessary.\n5.  **Finishing Touches:** After installation, the gaps and nail holes will be expertly caulked and filled, sanded smooth, and prepared for painting or staining, ensuring a flawless, integrated look.\n6.  **Cleanup:** Your professional will ensure the work area is thoroughly cleaned, leaving your home beautiful and tidy.\n\n**Practical Advice for Homeowners:**\n*   **Define Your Style:** Browse magazines or online galleries for inspiration. Do you prefer modern, traditional, or something in between?\n*   **Consider Material & Finish:** Think about the room''s function and your desired aesthetic. Will it be painted or stained?\n*   **Get Multiple Quotes:** Compare bids from several qualified professionals to ensure you''re getting competitive pricing and a clear understanding of the scope of work.\n*   **Check References & Portfolios:** Ask to see examples of previous trim work and read reviews to gauge the quality and reliability of the installer.\n*   **Communicate Clearly:** Discuss your expectations, timeline, and any specific concerns with your ProBuddy professional before the project begins.\n\nInvesting in professional trim and molding installation is an investment in your home''s beauty and longevity. Let ProBuddy connect you with skilled craftsmen who can bring your vision to life with unparalleled quality."
}}', updated_at = '2026-02-17T19:49:35.588Z' WHERE id = 'RDYVBpgYp2NoESnkkWonI';
UPDATE page_sections SET content = '{"title": "Frequently Asked Questions: Trim & Molding Installation", "items": [{"question": "What types of trim and molding do ProBuddy professionals install?", "answer": "Our skilled professionals are experienced in installing a wide variety of trim and molding styles, including baseboards, crown molding, door and window casing, chair rails, picture rails, and custom millwork. We work with various materials such as MDF, solid wood (pine, oak, maple), PVC, and composite options to match your home''s aesthetic and your budget. Whether you''re looking for a classic, modern, or custom look, we can help you select and install the perfect trim."}, {"question": "What is the typical process for a trim or molding installation project?", "answer": "A typical installation project begins with a detailed consultation and measurement to understand your vision and assess the scope. Next, we help with material selection (if you haven''t already purchased them). On installation day, our pros will prepare the area, carefully remove any existing trim (if applicable), and then precisely cut, fit, and secure the new molding. The process includes meticulous attention to detail like coping corners, filling nail holes, and caulking seams to ensure a seamless, paint-ready finish. We aim for minimal disruption and a clean worksite throughout."}, {"question": "How long does a trim installation project usually take?", "answer": "The duration of a trim installation project varies depending on several factors, including the size of the area, the complexity of the molding (e.g., intricate crown molding takes longer than simple baseboards), the material chosen, and the condition of your walls and floors. A single room with standard baseboards might be completed in a day, while a whole-house installation or complex custom work could take several days to a week. We provide an estimated timeline after our initial assessment."}, {"question": "Do I need to purchase 