        "answer": "The actual physical installation of a standby generator can typically be completed within 1 to 3 days, depending on the complexity of your home''s electrical system, the fuel source connection, and site preparation. However, the entire process, including initial consultation, load calculation, permit acquisition, generator ordering, and scheduling, can take several weeks to a few months. Factors like permit processing times, generator availability, and weather conditions can all influence the overall timeline."
