      {
        "question": "What kind of maintenance is required for a home standby generator after installation?",
        "answer": "To ensure reliability and longevity, standby generators require regular maintenance. This typically includes annual or bi-annual professional servicing, which involves changing the oil and filters, checking the battery, inspecting spark plugs, and ensuring all electrical and fuel connections are secure. Most modern standby generators also perform weekly or bi-weekly self-tests (a short run cycle) to ensure they are ready to operate. Following the manufacturer''s recommended maintenance schedule and using certified technicians is crucial for optimal performance and warranty validity."
      },
      {
        "question": "Will installing a new generator increase my home insurance premiums?",
        "answer": "Adding a permanent fixture like a standby generator typically increases the overall value of your home. As a result, your dwelling coverage on your home insurance policy might see a slight increase. However, some insurance providers may also offer discounts or credits for features that enhance safety or mitigate risks, such as preventing burst pipes from freezing during a power outage. It''s always best to contact your specific home insurance provider to inform them of the installation and inquire about any potential changes to your premiums or available discounts."
