UPDATE page_sections SET content = '{
    "faq": {
        "title": "Frequently Asked Questions About Generator Repair",
        "items": [
            {
                "question": "What are the common signs my home generator needs repair?",
                "answer": "Several indicators suggest your generator might require professional attention. These include failure to start during a power outage or test run, unusual noises (grinding, clunking, excessive vibration) during operation, visible leaks (oil, fuel, coolant), a burning smell, error codes displayed on the control panel, or inconsistent power output once running. If you notice any of these, it''s best to contact a qualified technician promptly."
            },
            {
                "question": "How often should I have my home generator serviced to prevent major repairs?",
                "answer": "Most manufacturers recommend annual maintenance for standby generators, regardless of how often they''ve run. This preventative service typically includes checking fluid levels, spark plugs, air filters, battery health, electrical connections, and general system diagnostics. Regular maintenance helps identify potential issues early, extends the lifespan of your unit, and ensures it''s ready to operate reliably when needed most, significantly reducing the likelihood of unexpected breakdowns and costly emergency repairs."
            },
            {
                "question": "Can I perform any DIY troubleshooting or repairs on my generator?",
                "answer": "While homeowners can perform basic checks like ensuring the generator has fuel, checking the circuit breaker, and verifying the battery is charged (if accessible), complex troubleshooting and repairs should always be left to certified professionals. Generators involve high voltage electricity, fuel systems, and complex mechanical components, posing significant safety risks if not handled correctly. Attempting DIY repairs without proper training and tools can void warranties, cause further damage, or lead to serious injury."
            },
            {
                "question": "What information should I have ready when I call for generator repair service?",
                "answer": "To help us diagnose the problem more efficiently, please have the following information ready: the make and model of your generator (usually found on a data plate), its approximate age, a description of the symptoms you''re experiencing (e.g., ''won''t start,'' ''making a loud noise,'' ''showing an error code F10''), when the problem started, and any recent maintenance performed. Providing this information upfront helps our technicians prepare for the service call."
            },
            {
                "question": "How long does a typical generator repair take, and what impacts the timeline?",
                "answer": "The duration of a generator repair varies greatly depending on the complexity of the issue. Minor repairs, like replacing a spark plug or a faulty sensor, might take an hour or two. More significant problems, such as engine component replacement or extensive electrical troubleshooting, could take several hours or even require multiple visits, especially if specialized parts need to be ordered. Factors like part availability, the age of the unit, and the specific diagnostic time also influence the overall timeline."
            },
            {
                "question": "What''s the typical cost range for generator repairs, and what factors influence it?",
                "answer": "Generator repair costs can range widely, from a few hundred dollars for minor issues (e.g., battery replacement, sensor repair) to several thousand for major component failures (e.g., engine overhaul, transfer switch replacement). Key factors influencing cost include the specific part needing replacement, the labor involved, the generator''s make and model (parts for premium brands can be more expensive), the complexity of the diagnosis, and whether the repair is an emergency or scheduled service. We provide a detailed estimate after a diagnostic visit."
            },
            {
                "question": "Do you service all brands and types of home generators?",
                "answer": "Our certified technicians are trained and experienced in servicing a wide range of home generator brands, including popular names like Generac, Kohler, Cummins, Briggs & Stratton, and more. We handle various types of home generators, from air-cooled to liquid-cooled, and whole-house standby units. If you have a less common brand, please mention it when you call, and we''ll confirm our ability to service it."
            }
        ]
    }
}', updated_at = '2026-02-17T19:50:10.443Z' WHERE id = '2VmkHtwoXU4UsS4NwrzJ-';
