        "answer": "The cost of switch and outlet repair can vary significantly based on several factors, including the type of switch or outlet (standard, dimmer, GFCI, smart outlet), the complexity of the issue, whether new wiring is required, and the number of units needing repair. Generally, a single standard switch or outlet repair might range from $100 to $300, while more complex issues, specialty outlets, or multiple repairs could be higher. We provide transparent, upfront pricing after a thorough diagnosis."
