        "question": "How long does a typical switch or outlet repair take?",
        "answer": "Most standard switch or outlet repairs are relatively quick, often taking between 30 minutes to 1.5 hours per unit, assuming no major underlying wiring issues. More complex problems, such as troubleshooting an intermittent fault, replacing multiple units, or addressing issues within the wall, can take longer. Our technician will provide an estimated timeframe after assessing the situation."
