      {
        "question": "What safety measures do your technicians take during an electrical repair?",
        "answer": "Safety is our top priority. Our licensed electricians always follow strict safety protocols, including shutting off power to the affected circuit at the main breaker before starting any work. They use insulated tools, wear appropriate personal protective equipment (PPE), and thoroughly test all connections and components before restoring power. All work is performed in compliance with national and local electrical codes to ensure the safety and reliability of your electrical system."
      }
    ]
  }
