    "text": "Is your old carpet looking worn, stained, or simply outdated? Perhaps you''re ready for a fresh start with new flooring, or hoping to uncover beautiful hardwood beneath. Whatever your reason, professional carpet removal is the crucial first step to transforming your space. While it might seem like a simple task, tearing up old carpet can be surprisingly labor-intensive, messy, and even uncover hidden issues.\n\n### Why Choose Professional Carpet Removal?\nHiring experts from ProBuddy ensures a smooth, efficient, and hassle-free experience. Our professionals come equipped with the right tools and expertise to handle carpets of all types and sizes, from small rooms to entire homes. We save you time, prevent potential injuries, and ensure proper disposal of old materials—often a logistical challenge for homeowners.\n\n### What to Expect During Your Carpet Removal Project:\n1.  **Initial Assessment:** Our team will assess the scope of the project, noting carpet type, room size, and any potential obstacles.\n2.  **Furniture Moving:** While we recommend clearing smaller items, our pros can assist with moving larger furniture to ensure full access to the carpeted areas.\n3.  **Carpet Lifting & Cutting:** Using specialized tools, we carefully cut the carpet into manageable strips and lift it, along with the tack strips.\n4.  **Padding Removal:** The underlying padding is removed, often revealing the subfloor beneath.\n5.  **Tack Strip & Staple Removal:** All remaining tack strips, staples, and debris are meticulously removed, leaving a clean subfloor.\n6.  **Subfloor Inspection:** This is a critical step! Our professionals will inspect your subfloor for any signs of damage, moisture, or mold, which need to be addressed before new flooring can be installed.\n7.  **Debris Haul-Away:** We don''t just remove your carpet; we haul away all the old materials, ensuring your home is left clean and ready for its next transformation.\n\n### Practical Advice for Homeowners:\n*   **Clear the Way:** Before our team arrives, remove small items, fragile decorations, and personal belongings from the rooms where carpet will be removed.\n*   **Discuss Disposal:** Confirm with your ProBuddy professional how the old carpet and padding will be disposed of. Our service typically includes eco-friendly disposal options.\n*   **Subfloor Expectations:** Be prepared for the possibility of discovering minor subfloor repairs needed, especially in older homes. This is a common occurrence and a necessary step for a smooth new flooring installation.\n*   **Ventilation:** The removal process can stir up dust and old fibers. We recommend good ventilation during and after the process.\n\nLet ProBuddy take the heavy lifting out of your home renovation project. Get a fresh start with a clean slate – your beautiful new floor awaits!"
  }
}', updated_at = '2026-02-17T19:50:54.368Z' WHERE id = 'PQUQ4Oefe0HJLsVPkxI5L';
UPDATE page_sections SET content = '{
  "faq": {
    "title": "Frequently Asked Questions About Carpet Removal",
    "items": [
      {
        "question": "Why should I hire a professional for carpet removal instead of doing it myself?",
        "answer": "While DIY carpet removal is possible, hiring a professional offers several advantages. It''s a physically demanding and time-consuming job, often requiring specialized tools like pry bars, utility knives, and knee kickers. Professionals ensure the safe removal of tack strips and staples, minimizing damage to your subfloor. We also handle the proper hauling and disposal of the old carpet, which can be bulky and subject to specific waste regulations and fees."
      },
      {
        "question": "What''s typically included in your professional carpet removal service?",
        "answer": "Our carpet removal service generally includes the complete removal of all carpet layers, the underlying padding, and the tack strips. We also handle the cleanup of loose debris, staples, and minor adhesive residue from the subfloor. Finally, we take care of hauling away and properly disposing of all the old carpeting and materials, leaving your space ready for new flooring installation or further preparation."
      },
      {
        "question": "How long does carpet removal usually take?",
        "answer": "The duration of carpet removal depends on several factors, including the size of the area, the type of carpet (e.g., glued down vs. stretched), the number of stairs, and the amount of furniture present. A single average-sized room (e.g., 10x12 ft) might take 1-2 hours, while a larger area or multiple rooms could take a half to a full day. Whole-house carpet removal can often span a full day or more. We''ll provide a more accurate estimate after assessing your specific project."
      },
      {
        "question": "What do I need to do to prepare my home for carpet removal?",
        "answer": "To ensure a smooth and efficient process, we ask that you clear the room(s) of all furniture, personal belongings, and fragile items. Remove any wall hangings or decor that might be in the way. Ensure a clear path for our team to work and to transport materials. If possible, secure pets in a separate area to keep them safe and out of the work zone. While we take precautions, covering nearby doorways or vents can help minimize dust spread to other areas."
