      {
        "question": "What happens to the old carpet once it''s removed?",
        "answer": "Once the old carpet, padding, and tack strips are removed, our team will roll them up and haul them away from your property. The materials are then transported to an approved waste facility for proper disposal. In some regions, carpet recycling options may be available, and we strive to utilize these environmentally friendly options where feasible and accessible, depending on the carpet material and local regulations."
