        "question": "Is carpet removal a messy or dusty process?",
        "answer": "Yes, carpet removal can be a messy and dusty process. Old carpets and padding accumulate years of dust, dirt, pet dander, and allergens, which can become airborne during removal. The process of pulling up carpet, padding, and especially tack strips can also generate debris. Our professionals take steps to minimize mess, such as using dust sheets, vacuums, and proper ventilation, but it''s advisable to be prepared for some level of dust and to plan for a thorough cleaning of the area afterward."
