UPDATE page_sections SET content = '{
  "content": {
    "title": "Upgrade Your Home: Expert Garage Door Installation & Replacement",
    "text": "A new garage door isn''t just about functionality; it''s a significant upgrade to your home''s curb appeal, security, and energy efficiency. Whether your old door is showing its age or you''re simply looking for a fresh new look, professional installation or replacement is a smart investment.\n\n**Why Upgrade Your Garage Door?**\nBeyond aesthetics, a modern garage door offers improved insulation, reducing energy costs, and enhanced security features for your peace of mind. It also significantly boosts your home''s market value, offering an excellent return on investment.\n\n**When to Consider Replacement**\nLook for signs like excessive noise during operation, slow or erratic movement, visible damage (dents, rust, cracks), frequent repairs, or simply an outdated aesthetic. If your door lacks modern safety features (like auto-reverse) or proper insulation, it might be time for an upgrade.\n\n**Why Hire a Professional?**\nGarage door installation is complex and can be dangerous due to heavy components and high-tension springs. Professionals ensure safe and correct installation, proper balance, and adherence to manufacturer warranties. They have the right tools, expertise, and experience to get the job done efficiently and safely, preventing future issues and ensuring your door operates smoothly for years to come.\n\n**What to Expect During Installation**\n1.  **Consultation & Selection:** Your journey begins with a consultation to discuss styles, materials (steel, wood, aluminum, composite), insulation options, and opener types. You''ll choose a door that complements your home''s architecture and meets your functional needs.\n2.  **Preparation & Removal:** On installation day, the old door, tracks, and hardware will be carefully removed and disposed of. The opening will be prepped for the new system.\n3.  **New Track & Hardware Installation:** New tracks, springs, cables, and rollers are meticulously installed. This step is crucial for the smooth and safe operation of your new door.\n4.  **Panel Assembly:** The new garage door panels are assembled section by section, ensuring a tight seal and proper alignment.\n5.  **Spring System Adjustment:** The torsion or extension springs are installed and precisely tensioned. This is the most critical and potentially dangerous part of the installation, requiring expert handling to ensure the door is perfectly balanced and operates safely.\n6.  **Opener Connection & Testing:** If you''re also upgrading your opener, it will be installed and connected. The entire system will then undergo rigorous testing to ensure smooth operation, proper safety reversal features, and correct alignment.\n7.  **Final Walkthrough:** Your installer will walk you through the new system, explaining its features, basic maintenance tips, and answering any questions you may have.\n\n**Practical Advice for Homeowners**\n*   **Research & Reviews:** Always choose licensed, insured, and reputable professionals. Check reviews and ask for references to ensure quality workmanship.\n*   **Get Multiple Quotes:** Compare proposals, not just prices. Understand what''s included in each quote, including labor, materials, and disposal fees.\n*   **Understand Warranty:** Ask about both the manufacturer''s warranty on the door and the installer''s warranty on labor. A good warranty offers peace of mind.\n*   **Consider Insulation (R-Value):** A higher R-value means better insulation, which can save you money on energy bills, especially if your garage is attached to your home or is used as a workspace.\n*   **Match Your Home''s Style:** The right garage door can dramatically enhance your home''s curb appeal. Consider materials, colors, and window options that complement your exterior architecture.\n*   **Ask About Maintenance:** Understand the basic maintenance required to keep your new door operating smoothly and safely for years to come.\n\nInvesting in professional garage door installation ensures safety, longevity, and optimal performance. Let ProBuddy connect you with trusted experts who can transform your home with a beautiful, functional, and secure new garage door."
  }
}', updated_at = '2026-02-17T19:52:01.068Z' WHERE id = 'A7zcuNnV8jE7G7AN34BEt';
UPDATE page_sections SET content = '{
    "title": "Garage Door Installation & Replacement FAQs",
    "items": [
        {
            "question": "How much does a new garage door installation or replacement typically cost?",
            "answer": "The cost of a new garage door varies significantly based on several factors. These include the material (steel, wood, aluminum, composite), insulation level, style, size (single vs. double door), the type of opener chosen, and any additional features like windows or decorative hardware. Labor costs, removal, and disposal of your old door are also factored in. While a basic steel door might be on the lower end, custom wood or highly insulated composite doors with advanced openers can be substantially more. We provide a detailed, itemized quote after an on-site consultation to ensure accuracy."
        },
        {
            "question": "How long does it take to install a new garage door?",
            "answer": "For a standard residential garage door replacement, the installation process typically takes between 3 to 6 hours. This timeframe can vary depending on the size of the door (a double door will take longer than a single door), the complexity of the installation, whether a new opener is being installed, and any unforeseen issues with the existing frame or structure. We strive to complete the job efficiently and with minimal disruption to your daily routine, ensuring all safety checks are performed before we leave."
        },
        {
            "question": "What types of garage doors are available, and which one is best for my home?",
            "answer": "There''s a wide range of garage door types and materials to choose from, each with its own benefits. Common materials include: \n\n*   **Steel:** Durable, low maintenance, and available in many styles and colors. Can be insulated for energy efficiency.\n*   **Wood:** Offers a classic, warm aesthetic but requires more maintenance (painting/staining).\n*   **Aluminum:** Lightweight, rust-resistant, and often used for modern designs with glass panels.\n*   **Composite (Wood Look):** Combines the look of wood with the durability and low maintenance of steel or fiberglass.\n\nThe ''best'' door depends on your budget, aesthetic preferences, desired insulation level, and local climate. During your consultation, we''ll discuss these options and help you select a door that perfectly complements your home''s architecture and meets your functional needs."
        },
        {
            "question": "Do I need a permit for garage door installation or replacement?",
            "answer": "In many areas, a permit is required for garage door installation or replacement, especially if it involves structural changes or if the new door varies significantly in size or type from the existing one. Building codes are in place to ensure safety and structural integrity. Our team is knowledgeable about local permitting requirements and can guide you through the process, or in many cases, handle the permit application on your behalf to ensure all work complies with local regulations."
        },
        {
            "question": "What happens to my old garage door after the replacement?",
            "answer": "As part of our comprehensive service, we will professionally remove and dispose of your old garage door and its components. This includes the door panels, tracks, springs, and any other associated hardware. We ensure that all discarded materials are handled responsibly and in an environmentally friendly manner, saving you the hassle of coordinating disposal yourself."
        },
        {
            "question": "What kind of maintenance is required for a new garage door?",
            "answer": "To ensure longevity and smooth operation, new garage doors benefit from regular, simple maintenance. We recommend visually inspecting your door monthly for any signs of wear and tear, lubricating moving parts (rollers, hinges, springs) with a silicone-based spray every 3-6 months, and checking the door''s balance annually. Additionally, we advise scheduling a professional tune-up and safety inspection once a year. This helps identify and address minor issues before they become major problems, keeping your door operating safely and efficiently."
        },
        {
            "question": "What warranty is provided with the new garage door and installation service?",
            "answer": "We stand by the quality of our products and workmanship. New garage doors typically come with a manufacturer''s warranty that covers the door panels, hardware, and components for a specified period, often ranging from 1 to 10 years or more, depending on the brand and model. In addition to the manufacturer''s warranty, we provide our own labor warranty on the installation service. We will clearly outline all warranty details, both manufacturer and labor, in your project quote so you have full peace of mind."
        }
    ]
}', updated_at = '2026-02-17T19:52:00.854Z' WHERE id = 'DWQT0tNMHbLMfsBRv87vh';
