      "answer": "The process generally begins with an initial consultation and precise measurements of your kitchen or bathroom. Once your material is selected and fabricated, our team will schedule the installation. This typically involves removing old countertops (if applicable), preparing the base cabinets, carefully placing and securing the new countertops, cutting precise openings for sinks and cooktops, sealing (for natural stone), and a thorough cleanup. We aim for minimal disruption to your daily routine."
