        "answer": "After a repair, proper maintenance is crucial to protect your countertop and prolong its life. We generally recommend using cutting boards, avoiding placing hot pots directly on the surface, wiping up spills immediately, and using appropriate cleaners for your specific countertop material. For natural stone, regular sealing (typically every 6-12 months) is essential to prevent staining and etching. Our technicians can provide specific care instructions tailored to your countertop type and the repair performed."
