UPDATE page_sections SET content = '{
    "faq": {
        "title": "Frequently Asked Questions About Deck & Porch Repair",
        "items": [
            {
                "question": "What types of deck or porch damage can ProBuddy professionals repair?",
                "answer": "ProBuddy connects you with skilled professionals who can address a wide range of deck and porch issues. This commonly includes repairing loose or wobbly railings, replacing rotten or cracked deck boards, fixing damaged stairs or risers, reinforcing wobbly support posts, repairing or replacing joists, addressing surface damage like splintering, and re-securing loose fasteners. Whether it''s structural integrity or cosmetic fixes, our pros are equipped to handle it."
            },
            {
                "question": "How do I know if my deck needs repair versus a full replacement?",
                "answer": "Determining whether to repair or replace often depends on the extent and nature of the damage. Minor issues like a few rotten boards, loose railings, or surface wear can typically be repaired. However, if there''s widespread structural rot, significant insect damage, multiple failing support posts, or if the deck is nearing the end of its expected lifespan (e.g., 20-30 years for wood), a full replacement might be more cost-effective and safer in the long run. Our professionals can assess your deck''s condition and provide an expert recommendation."
            },
            {
                "question": "What materials are typically used for deck and porch repairs?",
                "answer": "The materials used for repairs will often depend on your existing deck and your preferences. Common options include pressure-treated lumber (pine, fir), cedar, redwood, or composite decking materials. Our pros strive to match your current materials for a seamless look, but they can also discuss upgrading certain components to more durable or low-maintenance options if desired. They will ensure all materials meet local building codes and standards for safety and longevity."
            },
            {
                "question": "How long does a typical deck or porch repair project take?",
                "answer": "The duration of a deck or porch repair project varies significantly based on the scope of work, the severity of the damage, and weather conditions. Minor repairs, such as replacing a few boards or tightening railings, might take a few hours to a day. More extensive repairs, involving structural components, multiple sections, or staircase overhauls, could take several days to a week. Your ProBuddy professional will provide a detailed timeline after assessing your specific project."
