        "items": [
            {
                "question": "What exactly is finish carpentry, and how does it differ from rough carpentry?",
                "answer": "Finish carpentry focuses on the aesthetic and visible elements of a home, adding the ''finishing touches'' that enhance its beauty and character. This includes installing trim, baseboards, crown molding, door and window casings, wainscoting, custom built-ins, and fireplace mantels. Unlike rough carpentry, which deals with structural framing that is eventually covered, finish carpentry requires precision, attention to detail, and a high level of craftsmanship, as these elements are meant to be seen and admired."
