UPDATE page_sections SET content = '{"title": "Finish Carpentry: Tips for Homeowners", "tips": ["**Clearly Define Your Vision & Scope:** Before contacting professionals, gather inspiration photos (Pinterest, Houzz), sketch ideas, and list specific areas you want to enhance (e.g., crown molding, wainscoting, built-in shelves). The clearer your vision, the more accurate the quotes and the smoother the project outcome.", "**Prioritize Research & Vetting:** Don''t just pick the cheapest quote. Look for licensed, insured finish carpenters with strong portfolios and and references. Check online reviews and ask for examples of similar projects they''ve completed.", "**Understand Material Options & Budget Implications:** Discuss different wood species (pine, oak, maple, MDF), profiles, and finishes with potential pros. Each choice has a significant impact on cost, durability, and aesthetics. Be realistic about your budget for both materials and skilled labor.", "**Maintain Open Communication Throughout:** Establish a clear communication plan with your carpenter. Discuss project timelines, potential disruptions, and any questions or concerns immediately. Regular check-ins prevent misunderstandings and ensure the project stays on track.", "**Prepare Your Home for the Work:** Clear the work area of furniture and valuables. Finish carpentry creates dust, so protect adjacent areas with plastic sheeting or drop cloths. Ensure easy access to power outlets and a clear path for material delivery.", "**Conduct a Thorough Final Walkthrough:** Inspect every detail. Check for tight joints, smooth finishes, proper alignment, and no gaps or visible nail holes. Test any moving parts (e.g., cabinet doors). Address any imperfections or incomplete items before making final payment.", "**Understand Ongoing Maintenance:** Ask your carpenter for specific care instructions for your new finish carpentry. This might include recommendations for cleaning, touch-up paint/stain, and humidity control to prevent warping or cracking, especially for natural wood."]}', updated_at = '2026-02-17T19:53:13.102Z' WHERE id = '0jHRB2SweWMaj9e9wcQcs';
